crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a malicious shellcode loader. It decodes a hardcoded, obfuscated string by reversing it (_strrev) and converting the hexadecimal representation into binary (sub_1400026a0). The payload is then copied into an executable heap created via HeapCreate with the HEAP_CREATE_ENABLE_EXECUTE flag. To evade detection, it executes the shellcode using an unconventional method: it registers the shellcode buffer as a callback for a Thread Pool Wait object (CreateThreadpoolWait) and triggers execution by signaling an event (SetEvent). Additionally, the sample contains logic to modify memory protections to PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE using VirtualProtect, a common behavior in loaders and packers.
